DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(4,6,1);
$b1 = random(1,3,1);
$c1 = random(1,7,1);
$coef5 = 12;
$coef4 = 15*($a1-$b1);
$coef3 = 20*$a1*$b1;
$coef0 = $c1;
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Consider the function \( f(x) = $coef5 x^5 + $coef4 x^4 -
$coef3 x^3  + $coef0 \).
For this function there are four important intervals:
 \( (-\infty, A] \), \( [A,B] \),\( [B,C] \), and \( [C,\infty) \) where
 \( A \),  \( B \), and  \( C \) are the critical numbers.
 $BR
Find \( A \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = -$a1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
and  \( B \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = 0;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
and  \( C \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $b1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
At each critical number \( A \),  \( B \), and  \( C \) does \( f(x) \)
have a local min, a local max, or neither?
Type in your answer as LMIN, LMAX, or NEITHER.
$BR
At \( A \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "LMAX";
ANS(num_cmp($ans, strings=>['LMIN','LMAX','NEITHER']));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
At \( B \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "NEITHER";
ANS(num_cmp($ans, strings=>['LMIN','LMAX','NEITHER']));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
At \(C \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "LMIN";
ANS(num_cmp($ans, strings=>['LMIN','LMAX','NEITHER']));
ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
